contentrichtext.text: {{wiktionary|BH|Bh|.bh}} '''BH''', '''Bh''' or '''bh''' may refer to: {{TOCright}} ==Places== * [[Bahrain]]'s ISO 2-letter country code ** [[.bh]], the Internet country code top-level domain for Bahrain * [[Belize]]'s WMO and obsolete NATO country code digram * [[Belo Horizonte]], the capital of Minas Gerais, Brazil * [[Bihor County]], county in Romania * [[BH postcode area]], the United Kingdom postal area for the region in southern England which is served by Bournemouth postal sorting office * [[Beverly Hills]], a city in Los Angeles County, California, USA ==Religion== * [[B'ezrat hashem]] or B"H, Hebrew for "with God's help" * [[Before Hijra]], a moment in the Islamic calendar ==Other uses== * [[bh (digraph)]], a digraph in some writing systems * [[BH register]], the high byte of an X86 16-bit BX register * [[B&H Rail]]'s reporting mark * [[Beistegui Hermanos]], a Spanish bicycle manufacturer * [[Bihari language]]'s ISO 639-1 language code * [[Bohrium]], a chemical element * [[Broadcasting House (radio programme)|''Broadcasting House'' (radio programme)]] * [[Hawkair]]'s IATA code ==See also== *[[B&H (disambiguation)]] {{disambiguation}}
